test_invocation_justification:
go test -v ./...

# Or for individual packages:
cd package
go test -v
test_policy_justification:
New features are developed in feature branches and only merged if they fit the base requirements here: https://github.com/sahib/brig/blob/master/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md

There are of course additional requirements depending on the feature.
tests_are_added_justification: There is no evidence beside git version control.
warnings_justification: "make lint" runs a set of the most common linting tools over the complete code base including tests.
warnings_fixed_justification: PRs would not be merged if the linting processes triggers.
warnings_strict_justification: There are no compiler warnings in Go, only errors.
know_secure_design_justification: The theory was taught and practiced, but see answer below.
vulnerabilities_fixed_60_days_justificat: There is no tracking of unpatched vulnerabilities currently.
vulnerabilities_critical_fixed_justifica: There is no tracking of unpatched vulnerabilities currently.
static_analysis_justification:
gofmt -s -w
go fix -s
golint
misspell
gocyclo
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: There should be no buffer overflows, but tools like https://github.com/securego/gosec are currently not used.
static_analysis_often_justification: The interval is not daily, but happens on every feature merge at minimum.
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: There are no typical "assert" statements in Go, but most non-sensical events are being logged or propagated as error up in the tree.

contribution_justification: Projects on GitHub by default use issues and pull requests, as encouraged by documentation such as <https://guides.github.com/activities/contributing-to-open-source/>.

floss_license_osi_justification: The GPL-3.0 license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: https://github.com/AutolabJS/AutolabJS/wiki
repo_public_justification: Repository on GitHub, which provides public git repositories with URLs.
repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_interim_justification: The code commits on the GitHub repository contains all our code changes that occur between software releases.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_unique_justification: We use semantic versioning for all the software releases. Please see https://github.com/AutolabJS/AutolabJS/releases
report_responses_justification: https://github.com/AutolabJS/AutolabJS/issues All the user reported issues are given a response including a potential time frame for fixing them.
vulnerability_report_process_justificati: We use issues page for tracking the vulnerabilities. https://github.com/AutolabJS/AutolabJS/issues
vulnerability_report_private_justificati: We do not support private vulnerability reports
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: All the vulnerabilities are reported as GitHub issues and we usually respond in two days time.
build_common_tools_justification: We use Travis, Node.js and OpenSSH to build the software
build_floss_tools_justification: We use Travis to build the software.
test_invocation_justification: Tests can be run from shell terminal.
test_most_justification: We have not measured the test coverage yet.
test_policy_justification: We use unit and integration testing libraries of JavaScript language to test the new code commits.
tests_are_added_justification: Most of the recent commits (last seven months, i.e. from Jun 2017 to Jan 2018) have the tests put in. Please see https://github.com/AutolabJS/AutolabJS/commits/master
warnings_justification: We use code climate for code quality analysis. https://codeclimate.com/github/AutolabJS/AutolabJS
warnings_fixed_justification: All our development efforts in the last seven months (Jun 2017 - Jan 2018) have been towards addressing code quality warnings.
warnings_strict_justification: We do not add any new code that has code quality warnings. You can check the closed pull requests page (https://github.com/AutolabJS/AutolabJS/pulls?q=is%3Apr+is%3Aclosed) for evidence.
know_common_errors_justification: Some of our existing issues come in the nature of SQL injection possibilities. We have noted the vulnerabilities and are actively refactoring the source code to remove the vulnerabilities.
crypto_published_justification: We use NIST recommended minimum security mechanisms. Please see our OpenSSL configuration at: https://github.com/AutolabJS/AutolabJS/blob/master/deploy/openssl.cnf
crypto_call_justification: All our security certificates are produced by OpenSSL and are used by Express module of node.js server.
crypto_password_storage_justification: All the user password are halndled by GitLab (https://about.gitlab.com/). The administrator password is stored in plain text.
crypto_random_justification: We use the standard TLS mechanisms of WWW for secure communication.
delivery_unsigned_justification: TLS takes care of this problem.
vulnerabilities_fixed_60_days_justificat: We have a few SQL injection vulnerabilities that need fixing.
